---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Granny Flats Mt Eliza | Premium Design, Coastal-Spec | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Granny flat builders for Mt Eliza — premium homes, mature gardens, coastal salt-zone spec, Mornington Peninsula Shire DDO compliance. 1-bed, 2-bed, dual-occupancy. Free consultation."
  canonical="https://frankstongrannyflats.com.au/mt-eliza/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Mt Eliza &middot; Earimil &middot; Canadian Bay</span>
      <h1>Granny flats in <span class="accent">Mt Eliza</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Mt Eliza is the Peninsula&rsquo;s premium suburb. 1,000m&sup2;+ blocks, mature
        gardens, established homes, design-conscious owners. Granny flats here are
        rarely about the cheapest build &mdash; they&rsquo;re about a second dwelling
        that won&rsquo;t devalue the main residence.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Mt Eliza</span>
      <h2>The Mt Eliza granny flat story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Mornington Peninsula Shire &mdash; not Frankston City.</h3>
        <p>
          The boundary between Frankston City and Mornington Peninsula Shire runs along
          Humphries Road / Bentons Road. Mt Eliza sits in the <strong>Peninsula Shire</strong>,
          not Frankston City &mdash; meaning a different planning scheme, different
          ResCode application, and different DCPO design controls. Mt Eliza&rsquo;s
          Design and Development Overlay (DDO) is one of the stricter ones in the Shire
          and gives council discretion on height, mass and material choices.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Design integration with the existing home.</h3>
        <p>
          Mt Eliza buyers expect a granny flat to architecturally match the main house.
          Heritage Federation? Match the eave profile, weatherboard width, sash window
          proportions. Mid-century modern? Match the roof pitch, brick coursing,
          horizontal lines. We do every Mt Eliza project with a registered architect
          on the design phase &mdash; the few extra thousand at design saves $50K of
          rework when council asks for elevation changes.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">AS 4312 salt-spray zone &mdash; all of Mt Eliza.</h3>
        <p>
          Essentially all of Mt Eliza is within 3km of Port Phillip Bay and sits in
          AS 4312 &ldquo;moderate to severe&rdquo; salt-spray zone. Standard galvanised
          fixings will rust through within 8&ndash;12 years. We spec <strong>316-grade
          stainless</strong> on all external fasteners, hot-dip-galvanised structural
          steel, marine-grade silicone sealants, and powder-coated aluminium window
          framing as the floor for any Mt Eliza build.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Mt Eliza jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Architecturally-matched 1-bedroom granny flat 50m&sup2;, custom on-site, $170K&ndash;$220K</li>
          <li>2-bedroom dual-occupancy 100m&sup2; on a 1,500m&sup2; bay-view block, $230K&ndash;$300K</li>
          <li>Heritage-overlay-compliant rear extension/SDA build (additional approval layer)</li>
          <li>Pool-house / garden studio in keeping with existing landscaping, $60K&ndash;$120K</li>
          <li>Bayside-view granny flat with full coastal-spec (stainless, marine sealants, elevated subfloor)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/frankston-south/">Frankston South</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington/">Mornington</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/carrum-downs/">Carrum Downs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/seaford/">Seaford</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington-peninsula/">Mornington Peninsula</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Mt Eliza design consultation.</h2>
        <p>Architect-led design. Peninsula Shire DDO experience. Coastal-spec by default.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
